photos.date: June 1, 1940 (Same day as 0058—note boats on dock)
photos.description: Fishing derby weigh in 1940. There were often a couple derbies—usually with sponsors and prizes awarded. (Ken)

The main lodge, cedar log floats, and 16' Reinell cedar planked rental boats. The boat on the right was an inboard—it had a little air cooled Wisconsin engine and a rope/tiller steering system. Top speed was not enough to buck the big incoming tides but it was quiet and burned next to no gas. Note the garage building just to the left of the lodge. You can also see tents pitched to the right of the lodge, which is now State Park land. (Ken)

photos.description: This may not be Al but Al and Larry Johason were good summer friends as Al's family often stayed at Pt. Lawrence. They were dedicated fishermen, and Al Junior learned to fish at an early age. Assuming its Al I would guess this was his daughter.
